# RAG Q&A System

A fully local Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system built with Flask, FAISS, Ollama, and React. Upload any document and ask questions about it — all running on your own machine, no API costs.

---

## What It Does

1. **Upload** a document (`.txt`, `.pdf`, `.docx`)
2. System **chunks** it → **embeds** it → stores in **FAISS** vector database
3. You **ask a question** → system finds relevant chunks → **tinyllama generates an answer** with source citations

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Frontend | React, plain CSS |
| Backend | Flask (Python) |
| Vector Store | FAISS |
| Embeddings | nomic-embed-text via Ollama |
| LLM | tinyllama via Ollama |
| Auth | JWT tokens |
| Testing | pytest (28/28 passing) |

Everything runs **100% locally** — no OpenAI, no Google, no cloud costs.

---

## Project Structure

```
rag_project/
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py          # Flask app factory
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── health.py        # GET /health
