│   │   └── query.py         # POST /query
│   ├── core/
│   │   ├── config.py        # Settings (pydantic)
│   │   ├── chunker.py       # Text splitting
│   │   ├── embedder.py      # Embedding functions
│   │   ├── llm.py           # LLM answer generation
│   │   ├── prompt.py        # Prompt building
│   │   ├── retriever.py     # MMR reranking
│   │   └── vector_store.py  # FAISS store manager
│   └── middleware/
│       ├── auth.py          # JWT auth
│       └── rate_limit.py    # Rate limiting
├── tests/
│   ├── conftest.py
│   ├── unit/
│   │   ├── test_chunker.py
│   │   ├── test_embedder.py
│   │   ├── test_prompt.py
│   │   └── test_retriever.py
│   └── integration/
│       ├── test_ingest_api.py
│       └── test_query_api.py
rag-frontend/
└── src/
    └── App.js               # Full React UI
```

---

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.10+
- Node.js 18+
- [Ollama](https://ollama.com) installed and running

### Pull required Ollama models

```powershell
ollama pull nomic-embed-text
ollama pull tinyllama
```

---

## Setup

### 1. Clone and install Python dependencies

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\donar\OneDrive\Desktop\rag_project"
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 2. Install React dependencies

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\donar\OneDrive\Desktop\rag-frontend"
npm install
```

---

## Running the App

You need **3 terminals** open at the same time.

### Terminal 1 — Ollama
```powershell
ollama serve
```

### Terminal 2 — Flask Backend
```powershell
cd "C:\Users\donar\OneDrive\Desktop\rag_project"
$env:JWT_SECRET="your-real-secret"
flask --app app:create_app run --port 8000
```

### Terminal 3 — React Frontend
```powershell
cd "C:\Users\donar\OneDrive\Desktop\rag-frontend"
npm start
```

Then open **http://localhost:3000** in your browser.

---

## Getting a JWT Token

Tokens expire after 24 hours. Generate a new one with:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\donar\OneDrive\Desktop\rag_project"
$env:JWT_SECRET="your-real-secret"
python -c "from app.middleware.auth import create_access_token; print(create_access_token())"
```

Paste the `eyJ...` token into the Settings box in the UI and click **Save Token**.

---

## API Endpoints

### `GET /health`
Returns system status. No auth required.
```json
{ "status": "ok", "faiss_chunks": 8, "uptime_s": 120 }
```

### `POST /ingest`
Upload and index a document. Requires auth.
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/ingest \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
  -F "file=@document.pdf"
```
```json
{ "status": "indexed", "filename": "document.pdf", "doc_id": "abc123", "num_chunks": 5 }
```

### `POST /query`
Ask a question. Requires auth.
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/query \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"query": "How long do refunds take?", "top_k": 3}'
```
```json
{
  "answer": "Refunds take 5 business days...",
  "sources": [{ "text": "...", "score": 0.92, "source": "policy.pdf" }],
  "tokens_used": { "prompt": 61, "completion": 53 },
  "latency_ms": 1200
}
```

