---

## How It Works

```
User uploads file
      ↓
Text extracted (txt / pdf / docx)
      ↓
Split into chunks (500 tokens, 50 overlap)
      ↓
Each chunk embedded → 768-dim vector (nomic-embed-text)
      ↓
Vectors stored in FAISS index
      ↓
User asks question
      ↓
Question embedded → similarity search in FAISS
      ↓
Top-k chunks retrieved + MMR reranked
      ↓
Chunks + question sent to tinyllama
      ↓
Answer returned with source citations
```

---

## Notes

- Upload speed depends on your CPU — tinyllama runs locally so first response may take 10–15 seconds
- FAISS index persists to `data/` folder — your documents survive restarts
- To reset the index, delete `data/faiss_index` and `data/faiss_metadata.json`
- Change `JWT_SECRET` to something strong before sharing with anyone

